		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=98&FN=Quellious&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2172159&TN=Closure&CAT=Servers&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2172162&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Part 4</P><P><BR>Eryslai, The Kingdom of Wind (Plane of Air)</P><P>Millikin strolled through one of the corridors of Xegony's domain towards a library.  She had approached the goddess' inner sanctum and was turned away by Muzlakh, the gatekeeper of the goddess' inner sanctum.</P><P>"Be gone from here, mortal.  The fact that you serve Tunare means precious little here, so long as your kind continue to walk where they are neither wanted nor welcome."  The stormrider, a giant birdlike creatures with bee wings, hovered several feet in the air and scowled at the wood elf ranger.  But Millikin was not to be deterred so easily.  </P><P>"I have some questions."</P><P>"Then consult her chosen avatars of wind, dust, smoke, and mist."  Muzlakh replied.  "They are the ones appointed to determine if a mortal should be worthy of entering Xegony's presence.</P><P>"How do you think I got here in the first place?"  Millikin remarked.  Her patience was wearing thin.  She had spent weeks on end wandering the libraries and conversing with the various djinn, stormriders, and nilborien.  All of them claimed they had no idea of the globe's purpose that she had obtained from Fennin Ro's servant.  </P><P>"They said catastrophic events have been set in motion that may be my undoing."</P><P>"Then perhaps you should heed their warning, Feir`Dal."  Muzlakh growled.  </P><P>"Not until I find out what the globe of dancing flame is for."  Millikin answered.  The stormrider's eyes narrowed to slits.  "Stay here."   The stormrider turned and flew towards Xegony's assembly, and returned moments later, a book in hand.</P><P>"Read this and return it to any of the libraries here, mortal.  Do not leave this realm with that text in your possession."  The stormrider held out the book disdainfully towards the ranger.</P><P>"Thank you."  Millikin took the offered book.  There was no title on the cover.</P><P>"Now be gone from my sight."</P><P>Millikin turned and headed towards one of the libraries.  What she ended up reading she found quite unsettling.  She knew the story of Rallos Zek's attempt to murder the Rathe Council and his failure to do so was because as soon as one would fall another would rise up to take the place of the fallen.  The book detailed the precise reasons for Rallos' bid for power.  </P><P>The elemental gods had created a substance called the quintessence of the elements that enabled the user to alter time itself.   They had kept it hidden from the other gods in the care of the Rathe Council but somehow Rallos had learned of its existence and demanded they hand it over.  Obviously the elder gods refused, so Rallos Zek decided he would take it by force.  Once Rallos Zek was repelled and his followers were decimated by the panthenon, the elemental gods stated they would destroy the quintessence of the elements to prevent the possibility of Rallos Zek or another like minded individual would attempt to take it and abuse its power.  Xegony, the Triumvirate of Water, the Rathe Council, and Fennin Ro dismantled the quintessence and took back the portion of themself they contributed to its creation.  But the knowledge of how to create it was kept in tact.</P><P>Millikin stared down at the book in disbelief.  While she had been forbidden to leave with the book, nothing prevented her from copying its contents.  And so she copied down what she had just read into her journal before departing Eryslai, determined to return later once the information she had learned was kept safe.  </P><P>The deity of air was one of the most reclusive gods in the entire panthenon and so her entire assembly was none too pleased to see a wood elf shove past Muzlakh the Chosen and run straight towards their goddess' throne.  Several suits of armor that were gifted with the breath of life from Xegony drew their weapons and moved towards the intruder.  The elder goddess glanced in the direction of the disturbance.  Her minions were having some difficulty in apprehending the ranger who had abruptly ran in another direction, when she sensed the presence of others nearby.  She sighed inwardly and decided to bring this chase to an abrupt halt.  Tiny sylphs surrounded the ranger and she felt herself slowing down as a whirlwind engulfed her and she quickly found breathing impossible.  The ranger blacked out moments later.  Nuquernal Belegrodian, one of the elder djinn of Xegony's court, drew his dagger and moved to drive it through the ranger's back.</P><P>"Hold.  This ranger is here for a different purpose."  </P><P>"My Queen, she came with the others who are gathering for an assault."  Nuquernal slid the dagger back into his sash.  "Do you honestly think this one is any different from the other mortals?"</P><P>"We will soon find out."  </P><P>A castellan dragged the unconscious ranger across the field and dropped her on the ground a few feet in front of Xegony before returning to his post.  Millikin eventually stirred and pushed herself up to a sitting position trying to shrug aside the dizziness she was experiencing.  The sensation quickly faded away when she looked up to face the the unblinking gaze of Xegony.</P><P>"Millikin Erreene.  Why are you here?"</P><P>"How do you know who I am?  Millikin was startled.  Never before had any of Norrath's pantheon members known who she was, a thought she considered strange from ones who claimed near onmiscence.  "Never mind.  It's a stupid question."</P><P>"You are one of Tunare's adherents." It was more a statement than a question but the context was lost on the ranger.</P><P>"I don't know anymore.  It seems as if I don't exist as far as anyone is concerned."</P><P>"You are real enough.  Why are you here, Ranger?"  </P><P>"Why was I given this?"  Millikin reached for the medicine pouch worn around her neck and extracted the globe of dancing flame.  She held it up to Xegony.</P><P>"Fennin considered you worthy did he?"</P><P>"Worthy of what?"  Millikin's hand closed around the globe and she placed it back in her pouch.</P><P>"And you have displayed a remarkable level of determination and patience to reach me.  You will need this as well."  Millikin cautiously moved forward to see what the elemental god offered.  In the palm of her hand was a small white cloudlike object.  When she reached to touch it, her finger passed harmlessly through it.</P><P>"Just think about it in your hand."  Millikin glanced skeptically at the goddess then looked down to her hand.  Suddenly the tiny cloud appeared in her hand.  She glanced up to see Xegony was no longer holding the object.</P><P>"But what is it for?"</P><P>"The Quintessence is for time."  Xegony answered.  "Seek out the Rathe Council and the Triumvirate to complete it."<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
