		</font>
		<hr size="1">Part 6</P><P><BR>The Reef of Coirnav  (The Plane of Water)</P><P>The ranger's thoughts as to her foray into the Triumvirate of Water's realm were a chaotic jumble for the enchanter.  Unlike the other planes, Millikin never actually encountered E`ci, Povar, or Tarew Marr face to face.  They chose to speak through a singular proxy, an enormous kracken revered by the plane's denizens as Coirnav.  He refused to speak with mortals under any circumstances and sent swarms of crab-men called regrua, a wide assortment of aquatic animals, and elemental creatures called slarghilugs as well as water mephits to summarily slay any non-native.  When the leaders of each race were slain, Coirnav himself appeared and attempted to forcibly expel the unwanted visitors via magic when he failed and fell before the assault of the planar raiders, his spirit drifted away in the currents and momentarily engulfed the ranger.  Suddenly the waters chilled and left behind tiny chunks of ice.  Millikin took hold of the ice and abruptly felt herself shifted to the Plane of Tranquility.</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
