		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Part 10</P><P>Convocation</P><P>"Get up."  </P><P>Millikin sat up, still somewhat dazed.  The last thing she remembered was fighting the hydra named Quarm that was summoned by the elemental gods.</P><P>"You're barely presentable."  Valdayana critically inspected the ranger.</P><P>"I had other activities take precedent."  Millikin brushed the flecks of black ice from her clothing.</P><P>"You're going to attend a convocation of sorts.  Just remain silent and listen."  Valdayana stated briskly as she pushed the ranger towards the door.</P><P>"What's this for?"  Millikin dug in her heels to stop herself from being pushed forward any further.</P><P>"You'll see soon enough."  Valdayana replied.</P><P>Suddenly everything began to fall away before Millikin's eyes and she found herself looking into a dusky haze.  Then the area turned into a large assembly hall.  Then the deities of the Norrathian panthenon arrived, each accompanied by a minion who was not quite mortal.  Some of them Millikin visibly recognized, others she had no idea of whom they were.</P><P>"I told you this would happen, Father."  Solusek Ro's gloating pronouncement held a glimmer of barely concealed accusation.</P><P>"No one refuted that it was a possibility.  The issue at hand is the details of how it came to be."  Fennin Ro responded.</P><P>"Who cares?"  Rallos Zek growled.  "We should destroy her here and now and be done with it."  The god of war stood up and reached for the war axe leaning on the table beside him.  Tallon Zek, who had shrewdly been appraising Valdayana D`Varr, spoke quietly.</P><P>"Father, perhaps we should hear Fennin out first."  Tallon advised.</P><P>"I concur.  It might be best so we can prevent this sort of thing in the future."  Vallon Zek echoed his brother's sentiments.</P><P>"You are afraid of this mere dark elf.  Stand aside, cowards."  Rallos shoved his sons aside and lifted his axe and lifted it intending to cleave the enchanter in two.  Valdayana whispered an arcane phrase and suddenly Rallos' strength drained from his body.  He stumbled back and dropped his axe unable to lift it.  The god of war gave Valdayana a look of seething hatred and Innoruuk's chilling laughter echoed in the hall.  The goddess of nightmares glanced knowingly at  her father, Cazic Thule, who nodded almost imperceptibly.</P><P>"So you can defend yourself from direct physical harm.  How is your mental stability?" Terris Thule gestured and tendrils of energy emerged from the ground and surrounded the dark elf enchanter searching for her innermost fears.  Suddenly the tendrils whiplashed back towards Terris, who's eyes widened in surprise as they disappeared.</P><P>"Quite stable."  Valdayana gazed impassively at the tall woman before turning to address the Seventh Hammer.  "Are these attempts at petty one-upmanship concluded?"  </P><P>"Well there is the question of how a new demi-god is so powerful."  Solusek Ro observed.</P><P>"She stole her power."  Bristlebane chimed in, grinning.</P><P>"Stolen?!"  The surprise of several gods was evident.</P><P>"Misplaced is a more accurate term."  Valdayana commented absently.</P><P>"Misplaced by whom?"  Mithaniel Marr inquired.</P><P>"It should be evident I think.  The elemental elders themselves."</P><P>"You lie."  Saryrn hissed.</P><P>"It's true."  Millikin interjected.  "They imbued their essence into me as part of your prison for Zebuxoruk."</P><P>"We reclaimed that power from you though."  Fennin Ro responded in surprise.</P><P>"Not all of it."  Valdayana answered.</P><P>"I demand to know what this Feir`Dal of yours has to do with all of this, Tunare."  Rallos Zek roared at the goddess of nature.  "She has been a perpetual thorn in my side since this entire fiasco started."  Tunare looked from Millikin to Rallos Zek to Xegony.</P><P>"It's not my place to say."</P><P>"Tunare abandoned her long ago."  Valdayana remarked.  "Isn't that true?"</P><P>Millikin's eyes widened in shock when there was no response forthcoming from the elven deity.</P><P>"It's okay to hate her, mortal."  Innoruuk gloated.  "I certainly do."</P><P>"If I abandoned her as you claim, then who granted her the ability to wield divine magic."</P><P>"Did you not gift your creations with the ability to attune themself to nature?"  Valdayana remarked dryly.  "You haven't bothered directly with the development of the lesser elves in eons.  You left them to their own fate and rarely meddled even while Tunaria burned."</P><P>"Astute observations, Valdayana D`Varr."  Saryrn uttered.  "It still doesn't answer the question as to how you achieved divinity."</P><P>"The ranger told you.  The elemental gods imbued some of their power into her and I took it for myself."  </P><P>"Impossible!"  Rallos Zek roared.  "They managed to summon Quarm!"</P><P>"Did you think I was stupid enough to take every ounce of power.  I left some of it so your machinations played out as you intended.  I'm not such a fool as to think godhood should be up for grabs to every sword swinging idiot or incompetent spellcaster that traipses through Norrath."  </P><P>"Why don't you just reclaim your powers from this upstart?"  Cazic Thule turned to face the elemental elder gods.</P><P>"We cannot."  The Rathe Council intoned.  "She took precautions to ensure they could not be taken from her using unknown magicks."</P><P>"She thought of everything."  Tallon Zek remarked offhandedly.</P><P>"You manipulated that ranger solely to acquire divinity."  Mithaniel Marr looked sharply at Valdayana D`Varr.</P><P>"Yes, and in the process I forwarded your plans to keep the collective mortals from gaining Zebuxoruk's knowledge."  Valdayana answered.  </P><P>"Not exactly the most honorable means to acquire an end."  Mithaniel remarked.</P><P>"Don't act like she wasn't already being manipulated by others.  When your compatriots were finished with her they left her to drift into oblivion."  Valdayana gazed coldly at the paladin god.</P><P>"The Tribunal is of the opinion that Valdayana D`Varr has earned her place among our ranks as a deity through the use of intrigue, manipulation, and acquired hidden lore.  She has broken no laws of universal balance and has acted to promote such."  The Seventh Hammer pronounced solemnly.</P><P>"So typical of the Tribunal."  Innoruuk remarked contemptuously.</P><P>"The debating raged back and forth for what seemed like hours.  The more pragmatic gods agreed that it would be better to have her amongst her ranks as opposed to running the risk of  a rogue power operating against them.  Eventually the convocation dispersed, taking their minions with them.</P><P>"Why did you take me to this?"  </P><P>"Because these convocations required a non-deific observer on behalf of each deity present."  Valdayana answered.  "And you needed to know where you stand amongst the pantheon."</P><P>"They don't care about anyone."</P><P>"We'll talk later when you aren't so angry."  </P><P>"I'm not angry..."  Millikin started but was suddenly left standing alone in the Greater Faydark.</P><P>~~~~~</P><P>Valdayana D'Varr is the sole property of her creator used for role playing purposes with prior consent. Do not duplicate. </P><P>Millikin Erreene is the sole property of her creator used for role playing purposes. Do not duplicate. <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
